edu.brown.cs.gk16

Class Interpreter

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.brown.cs.gk16.Interpreter

  • public class Interpreter
extends Object
    This class represents an interpreter that generates a REPL to read in user input. In its function eval, it then parses the commands given by the user and interprets them according to other private functions listed in the class (error-checking in the process).

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      Interpreter()
      The interpreter has a star object which allows for functionality in interpreting the commands stars, neighbors, and radius.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Interpreter

        public Interpreter()
        The interpreter has a star object which allows for functionality in interpreting the commands stars, neighbors, and radius. To add further functionality, one could create a new object that defines methods to interpret new commands — and each new command could be added to the if else loop in the eval function which is relatively extensible.
